       <h2>About<br></h2>
        <p class='p_font_size'>
        CrowdPics began as a way to allow wedding guests to participate in the creation of memories, without flooding social media/photo-sharing sites with pictures that the Happy Couple *ahem*...might not fully appreciate. (Sorry, Uncle Pete, your photo skillz aren't as incredible as you seem to think.) Essentially, CrowdPics was going to replace the disposable cameras placed on guests' tables. </p>
        <p class='p_font_size'>However, the CrowdPics team soon realized that an application like this had power beyond maintaining the purity of images from a couple's Big Day. It could also be used to ensure that the rowdiness of parties remains amongst those actually present at said party. It would also eliminate the problem of the Forgetful Photographer--the guy or gal who never seems to remember to share precious, captured moments. You know, like puke pics and stuff.</p>
        <p class='p_font_size'>Click <a href="#learn_more">here</a> to learn more about how CrowdPics was built, including the struggles and obstacles faced by the CP Team. We're excited to have you join us as you Crowdsource, Curate, and Create!</p>


  </div>
</div>
</section>

