    <h2>Learn More</h2>
      <div class='lp_lm_right_text col-md-6'>
      <p class='p_font_size'>CrowdPics is a crowdsourcing image app that allows multiple users to contribute by simply entering an event code and snapping away.  It allows the host to obtain pictures from guests, resulting in multiple and varied perspectives of an event. On the mobile side, CrowdPics uses Apple's new programming language, Swift--just a month old at the time of development. For the web, the team dove into Ruby/Rails, JavaScript/jQuery/AJAX, and a variety of other tools and libraries in order to create a fluid and enjoyable experience, as users pore over their photos.</p>
      <p class='p_font_size'>Obstacles arose that might have thwarted lesser teams, but the CrowdPics crew has magical thwart-proof powers, so they got the job done. Rails' Asset Pipeline? Pffft...child's play! And nice try, Version Control, these fellas know Git! The boys relied on their ability to search the web for answers, tap into the Chicago developer community, and lean on each other in order to overcome would-be disasters. The result isn't perfect, but the journey proved enlightening, educational, and fun. Thank you for checking us out. Now, go take some Pics!
      </p>

